x4freetext: Monte Carlo code MORSE-DD used for neutron spectra
to 330 keV.  The beam current was 1.5 mA.
Water cooled Ti-T target. Neutron yield at
Source neutron spectra calculated by MORSE-DD at angles
5 GeLi detectors were used. Two of these served
as standard detectors, and the absolute efficiency of
these were determined with standard gamma-ray sources.
neutrons between 13.3 to 15.0 MeV. Determined relative
to MONIT1. Used as neutron flux monitor.
Was used as a substandard for half-lives longer than
Determined relative to MONIT1 with uncertainty 4.3%.
In COMMON block the value of MONIT1 and MONIT3  at
Separated isotopes were used. If the sample was
powder, it (about 50.mg weight) was wrapped in a
cartridge paper with effective area of 1 cm2.
Samples were positioned at a distance of 10 cm from the
target, in the angular interval 0 - 165 degrees, thus
Samples with short-lived activities were transported
along the pneumatic tube with a transfer time of
Two Nb foils of 10.mm x 10.mm x 0.1 mm for one
Corrections were applied for count loss due to
summation of cascade gammas, self-absorption in the
samples, fluctuation of the neutron flux during
irradiation, and for contribution of low energy
Error of sample weight less than 0.1%
Error of correction for mean source
Error of correction for cascade summing
Data taken from Table 5 of JAERI-1312,1988
S.W. Flags added to numerous  subents.
SM: Data error in SAN064 corrected. Errors
structure given and DATA-ERR to ERR-T changed.
M.M. Misprint in Subent 096 was corrected.
Free text was corrected to be human-readable.
Monitors values were added. Misprints in decay data
were corrected in several Subents. Information in
SD: REACTION code in Subent 106 was
corrected. ERR-ANALYS was corrected. Minor corrections.
SD: STATUS `COREL` added to several Subents
The accuracy of data presentation  has been revised.
